#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:3
msgid "Building from source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:6
msgid ""
"If you are building the latest development version of Pyodide from the "
"`main` branch, please make sure to follow the build instructions from the "
"dev version of the documentation at [pyodide.org/en/latest/](https://pyodide."
"org/en/latest/development/building-from-sources.html)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:12
msgid "Pyodide can be built from sources on different platforms,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:14
msgid ""
"on **Linux** it is easiest using the Pyodide Docker image. This approach "
"works with any native operating system as long as Docker is installed. You "
"can also build on your native Linux OS if the correct build prerequisites "
"are installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:18
msgid ""
"on **MacOS** it is recommended to install dependencies via conda-forge or "
"using Homebrew, particularly with the M1 ARM CPU. Building with Docker is "
"possible but very slow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:21
msgid ""
"It is not possible to build on **Windows**, but you can use [Windows "
"Subsystem for Linux](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install-"
"win10) to create a Linux build environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:25
msgid "Build instructions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:27
msgid ""
"The Pyodide repository has a git submodule called `pyodide-build`. Make sure "
"to do a recursive clone:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:30
msgid "git clone --recursive https://github.com/pyodide/pyodide\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:34
msgid ""
"or if you have already cloned the Pyodide repository without the `--"
"recursive` flag, you may initialize the submodule with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:37
msgid "git submodule update --init\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:41
msgid ""
"If you change git branches, make sure you update `pyodide-build` with `git "
"submodule update`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:44
msgid "Using Docker"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:46
msgid ""
"We provide a Debian-based x86_64 Docker image ([`pyodide/pyodide-env`]"
"(https://hub.docker.com/r/pyodide/pyodide-env)) on Docker Hub with the "
"dependencies already installed to make it easier to build Pyodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:52
msgid ""
"These Docker images are also available from the Github packages at [`github."
"com/orgs/pyodide/packages`](https://github.com/orgs/pyodide/packages)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:56
msgid "Install Docker"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:58
msgid "From a git checkout of Pyodide, run `./run_docker`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:60
msgid "Run `make` to build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:63
msgid ""
"You can control the resources allocated to the build by setting the env vars "
"`EMSDK_NUM_CORE`, `EMCC_CORES` and `PYODIDE_JOBS` (the default for each is "
"4)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:68
msgid ""
"If running `make` deterministically stops at some point, increasing the "
"maximum RAM usage available to the docker container might help. (The RAM "
"available to the container is different from the physical RAM capacity of "
"the machine.) Ideally, at least 3 GB of RAM should be available to the "
"docker container to build Pyodide smoothly. These settings can be changed "
"via Docker preferences (see [here](https://stackoverflow.com/"
"questions/44533319/how-to-assign-more-memory-to-docker-container))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:76
msgid ""
"You can edit the files in the shared `pyodide` source folder on your host "
"machine (outside of Docker), and then repeatedly run `make` inside the "
"Docker environment to test your changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:80
msgid "Using the \"Docker\" dev container"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:82
msgid ""
"We provide a dev container configuration that is equivalent to the use of `./"
"run_docker` script. It can be used in [Visual Studio Code](https://code."
"visualstudio.com/docs/devcontainers/containers) and on [GitHub Codespaces]"
"(https://docs.github.com/en/codespaces/overview). When prompted, select "
"\"Docker\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:87
msgid "Using the \"Conda\" dev container"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:89
msgid ""
"We provide another dev container configuration that corresponds to the "
"\"Linux with conda\" method described below. When [Visual Studio Code]"
"(https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/devcontainers/containers) or [GitHub "
"Codespaces](https://docs.github.com/en/codespaces/overview) prompts for the "
"dev container configuration, select \"Conda\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:94
msgid "Using `make`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:96
msgid ""
"Make sure the prerequisites for [emsdk](https://github.com/emscripten-core/"
"emsdk) are installed. Pyodide will build a custom, patched version of emsdk, "
"so there is no need to build it yourself prior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:101
msgid ""
"You need Python 3.14.2 to run the build scripts. To make sure that the "
"correct Python is used during the build it is recommended to use a [virtual "
"environment](https://packaging.python.org/guides/installing-using-pip-and-"
"virtual-environments/#creating-a-virtual-environment) or a conda environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:0
msgid "Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:110
msgid "To build on Linux, you need:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:112
msgid ""
"A working native compiler toolchain, enough to build [CPython](https://"
"devguide.python.org/getting-started/setup-building/index.html#linux)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:114
msgid "CMake (required to install Emscripten)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:0
msgid "Linux with conda"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:121
msgid ""
"You would need a working native compiler toolchain, enough to build   "
"[CPython](https://devguide.python.org/getting-started/setup-building/index."
"html#linux), for example,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:123
msgid "`apt install build-essential` on Debian based systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:124
msgid ""
"Conda which can be installed from [MiniForge](https://github.com/conda-forge/"
"miniforge)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:126
#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:140
msgid ""
"Then install the required Python version and other build dependencies in a "
"separate conda environment,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:128
#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:142
msgid ""
"conda env create -f environment.yml\n"
"conda activate pyodide-env\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:0
msgid "macOS with conda"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:134
msgid "You would need,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:135
msgid "System libraries in the root directory: `xcode-select --install`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:137
msgid ""
"Conda which can be installed using [Miniforge](https://github.com/conda-"
"forge/miniforge) (both for Intel and M1 CPU)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:0
msgid "macOS with Homebrew"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:149
msgid "To build on macOS with Homebrew, you need:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:151
msgid "System command line tools: `xcode-select --install`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:153
msgid "[Homebrew](https://brew.sh/) for installing dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:154
msgid ""
"Pyodide requires CMake3 but Homebrew installs CMake4. Use pip for cmake `pip "
"install cmake==3.31`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:156
msgid ""
"`brew install coreutils cmake autoconf automake libtool libffi ccache wget "
"rustup-init`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:157
msgid ""
"Initialize Rust (needed for building test-rust-* packages): `rustup-init`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:158
msgid ""
"Install the GNU patch and GNU sed (`brew install gpatch gnu-sed`) and re-"
"defining them temporarily as [`patch`](https://formulae.brew.sh/formula/"
"gpatch) and [`sed`](https://formulae.brew.sh/formula/gnu-sed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:167
msgid ""
"If you encounter issues with the requirements, it is useful to check the "
"exact list in the [Dockerfile](https://github.com/pyodide/pyodide/blob/main/"
"Dockerfile) which is tested in the CI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:173
msgid ""
"You can install the Python dependencies from the requirement file at the "
"root of Pyodide folder: `pip install -r requirements.txt`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:176
msgid "After installing the build prerequisites, run from the command line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:178
msgid "make\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:184
msgid "Building a full Pyodide distribution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:186
msgid ""
"By running `make`, you build a minimal Pyodide distribution that includes "
"only the core packages. Pyodide contains a large number of packages, and "
"building all of them takes a long time. If you want to build a full "
"distribution, or make a custom distribution with a subset of packages, there "
"are two options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:191
msgid "Use pre-built packages from the `pyodide-recipes` repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:193
msgid ""
"Packages included in the Pyodide distribution are built separately and "
"stored in the [`pyodide-recipes`](https://github.com/pyodide/pyodide-"
"recipes) repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:196
msgid ""
"Setting `ENABLE_PREBUILT_PACKAGES` environment variable to `1` will download "
"and install pre-built packages from the `pyodide-recipes` repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:199
msgid "ENABLE_PREBUILT_PACKAGES=1 make\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:203
msgid "Build a subset of packages from the `pyodide-recipes` repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:205
msgid ""
"If you want to build a subset of packages, you can clone the `pyodide-"
"recipes` repository and build the packages you need."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:208
msgid ""
"git clone https://github.com/pyodide/pyodide-recipes\n"
"\n"
"# Build the packages you need\n"
"pyodide build-recipes \"numpy, scipy, toolz, attrs\" --recipe-dir pyodide-"
"recipes/packages --install\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:215
msgid ""
"Dependencies of the listed packages will be built automatically as well. The "
"package names must match the folder names in `pyodide-recipes/packages` "
"exactly; in particular they are case-sensitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:219
msgid ""
"There are also some meta-packages that can be used to build a subset of "
"packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:221
msgid ""
"\"tag:min-scipy-stack\": includes the \"core\" meta-package as well as some "
"core packages from the Scientific Python stack and their dependencies: "
"\"numpy\", \"scipy\", \"pandas\", \"matplotlib\", \"scikit-learn\", "
"\"joblib\", \"pytest\". This option is non exhaustive and is mainly intended "
"to make build faster while testing a diverse set of scientific packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:226
msgid "\"tag:library\": includes all shared and static libraries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:227
msgid ""
"\"tag:shared_library\": includes all shared libraries. Added in conjunction "
"with the \"library\" tag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:229
msgid ""
"\"tag:static_library\": includes all static libraries. Added in conjunction "
"with the \"library\" tag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:231
msgid ""
"\"tag:pyodide-test\": includes all packages built to test the Pyodide build "
"system's behaviour."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:233
msgid ""
"\"tag:rust\": includes all packages that require a Rust toolchain to build, "
"and their dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:235
msgid "\"\\*\" builds all packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:236
msgid "You can exclude a package by prefixing it with \"!\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:238
msgid "micropip is always automatically included."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:240
msgid "Environment variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:242
msgid "The following environment variables additionally impact the build:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:244
msgid ""
"`PYODIDE_JOBS`: the `-j` option passed to the `emmake make` command when "
"applicable for parallel compilation. Default: 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:246
msgid ""
"`PYODIDE_BASE_URL`: Base URL where Pyodide packages are deployed. It must "
"end with a trailing `/`. Default: `./` to load Pyodide packages from the "
"same base URL path as where `pyodide.js` is located. Example: `https://cdn."
"jsdelivr.net/pyodide/v314.0.2/full/`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:250
msgid "`EXTRA_CFLAGS`: Add extra compilation flags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:251
msgid "`EXTRA_LDFLAGS`: Add extra linker flags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:253
msgid ""
"Setting `EXTRA_CFLAGS=\"-D DEBUG_F\"` provides detailed diagnostic "
"information whenever error branches are taken inside the Pyodide core code. "
"These error messages are frequently helpful even when the problem is a fatal "
"configuration problem and Pyodide cannot even be initialized. These error "
"branches occur also in correctly working code, but they are relatively "
"uncommon so in practice the amount of noise generated isn't too large. The "
"shorthand `make debug` automatically sets this flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-from-sources.md:261
msgid ""
"In certain cases, setting `EXTRA_LDFLAGS=\"-s ASSERTIONS=1` or "
"`ASSERTIONS=2` can also be helpful, but this slows down the linking and the "
"runtime speed of Pyodide a lot and generates a large amount of noise in the "
"console."
msgstr ""
